The 'srcmod' consists of two key parts:

    * Application files 
    * Source module files

The application files make up collection of tools used to manage a given source
module. Such tools currently include:

    * ./authors 
    * ./build 
    * ./changelog 
    * ./files 
    * ./install 
    * ./package 
    * ./readme 
    * ./setup 
    * ./tasks 
    * ./uninstall 

The source module files consist of everything that belongs to a given source
module. In the current release, these include:

    * Descriptors 

        * API 
        * AUTHORS 
        * BACKGROUND 
        * BUILD 
        * CHANGELOG 
        * DEFECTS 
        * DESCRIPTION 
        * DESIGN
        * EXAMPLES
        * FEATURES 
        * INSTALL 
        * LICENSE
        * README 
        * REQUIREMENTS 
        * SOURCES 
        * TASKS 
        * TEST 
        * VERSION 

    * Templates

        * template.bash 
        * template.c 
        * template.c++ 
        * template.gitignore 
        * template.java 
        * template.python 
        * template.ruby
